h3. Problem Definition
The recommended Isolation Level configuration for SQL server according to our [connecting JIRA to SQL Server|https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver071/connecting-jira-applications-to-sql-server-2014-808761244.html] documentation is setting READ_COMMITTED_SNAPSHOT to ON. Failing to do this may in some scenarios have severe impact as described here [JIRA is running out of database connections frequently on MS SQL Server|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRAKB/JIRA+is+running+out+of+database+connections+frequently+on+MS+SQL+Server]. Currently, there is no warning from JIRA when you don't have the Isolation Level configured correctly.

h3. Suggested Solution
Add a healthcheck function that checks that the correct isolation level is set, and gives a warning if it isn't. This could be implemented using an SQL query such as the following for instance:
{code}SELECT is_read_committed_snapshot_on FROM sys.databases WHERE name= 'JIRA-DATABASE';
{code}

